{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"43e21548-304e-41cd-bae1-01f439de0783","content":"Here's the equivalent command using Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) arguments passed after `--`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key mappings:**\n\n| VSTest | MTP (after `--`) |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Prerequisites** — your test project needs these packages:\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild` (enables `dotnet test` → MTP bridge)\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` (for `--report-trx`)\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` (for `--coverage`)\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` / `HangDump`\n\nThe `--filter` stays *before* `--` since `dotnet test` forwards it to MTP automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9727a5d3-1729-4f71-b855-d0370a242bd4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences between VSTest and MTP:\n- `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` \n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-coverage` with coverage settings\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\n\n- With .NET 8, you'll need to pass MTP arguments after `--` when using `dotnet test`, or run the test executable directly, though native MTP support is more streamlined in .NET 9 SDK. I'm working through the correct command syntax for MTP on .NET 8, mapping the old VSTest arguments to their MTP equivalents—`--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`, `--blame-hang` becomes `--hangdump`, and the timeout format adjusts accordingly, with all MTP-specific flags going after the `--` separator.","outputTokens":1251,"requestId":"0420:1CF5FA:1DF3D7D:21C9A7C:69E81AAD"},"id":"ad31683a-2300-4a0c-9d31-6eb5fd4d9279","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:48:04.019Z","parentId":"cf48b42e-07d1-4dcf-9ed4-11bb9d924ff5"}
